  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior / Manager Human Resources",
  "description": "<p><strong>Tasks</strong></p><ul><li>Develop and review the Porsche Asia Pacific (\"PAP\") HR strategy in alignment with the global HR strategy, market-specific requirements and potentials, as well as the Volkswagen group HR approach to Asia Pacific</li><li>Drive HR transformation initiatives leveraging digitalisation, reviewing and coordinating the implementation of internal enhancement along the employee life cycle</li><li>Manage employee compensation, disciplinary matters, talent and performance management, and recognition</li><li>Identify, evaluate, and foster best practice sharing and cross-functional synergies at PAP in conjunction with headquarters, as well as other subsidiaries to enhance employee experience</li><li>Manage HR compliance and integrity, ensure clear communication and equitable application of policies and procedures in accordance with Group standards</li><li>Facilitate and develop an understanding and application of modern leadership and support effective cross-departmental collaboration</li></ul><p><br />Qualifications</p><ul><li>University degree in Business Administration, Human Resources, Communication Studies, Psychology (or similar)</li><li>Minimum 8 years relevant HR experience in Employee Relations, Recruitment, Selection, Training and Organisational Development, Compensation and Benefits, Compliance</li><li>Good knowledge of the specific of employment law</li><li>Proven professional experience in project management, multi-stakeholder relationship management and implementation of staff engagement initiatives</li><li>Fluency in written and spoken English with excellent communication skills, and ability to motivate and inspire the team</li><li>Preferably previous professional experience in multi-cultural environment</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 8,
